{"TopicId":137830,"ForumId":34,"TopicTitle":"[1.9.x] Mouse Aim Flight (1.1.3) - Pilot airplanes with your mouse!","CreatedByName":"tetryds","CreatedById":50204,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-23T07:17:49Z","PageNum":12,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Sticky3002","CreatedById":190350,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-05-04T18:53:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223964145\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022137830\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221619844094\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022210939\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AtomicKepler\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 5/1/2021 at 1:41 AM, AtomicKepler said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe idea with this is that since mouse aim flight is also binded to roll for all of its modes, it makes flying very interesting, when you try to use MAF for a long and precise knife edge of an inverted low pass or what. it isn\u0027t possible, because of the auto correction of the roll axis.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOne solution for this might be using your keyboard. MAF binds controls to the mouse, but using WASD (and QE for roll) is still possible. Granted, this makes the flight quite jittery, but it\u0027s one way to do it. You might get rid of the jitteryness if you make your plane aerodynamically acrobatic\u00A0enough.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AtomicKepler","CreatedById":210939,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-05-06T13:08:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah for\u00A0 now, we have some problems...\u003Cbr\u003E\nI need extreme precision... it don\u0027t really work well.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KerbalSofaProgram","CreatedById":188784,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-05-27T21:59:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\ni can\u0027t seem to find this on \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003Eckan\u003C/abbr\u003E, even after manually downloading it doesn\u0027t show up in my list of installed mods. also...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223900947\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022137830\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221609283246\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002292207\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Beetlecat\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 12/29/2020 at 6:07 PM, Beetlecat said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd, likewise in 1.11, though I didn\u0027t check the console to see if anything was spamming in-game.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nhave you had any issues since? i\u0027m about to start up ksp 1.11.2 with mauz aim flite so i was just wondering\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Caerfinon","CreatedById":207619,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-05-27T22:44:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223980165\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022137830\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221622152793\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022188784\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022KerbalSofaProgram\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n41 minutes ago, KerbalSofaProgram said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ni can\u0027t seem to find this on \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003Eckan\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nit is not indexed on \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E. Just GitHub and Curse Forge\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KerbalSofaProgram","CreatedById":188784,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-05-28T00:53:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223980198\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022137830\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221622155441\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022207619\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Caerfinon\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Caerfinon said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nit is not indexed on \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E. Just GitHub and Curse Forge\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthanks for the reply. like i mentioned i already plopped it in the ksp matrix and was about to try it out. i just wasn\u0027t sure if it was supposed to be on there, so i figured i ought to mention it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SnipersLaww","CreatedById":212916,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-05T18:08:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nis there a way to get the mouse circle and pointer\u00A0to appear for this if it isnt visible?\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tetryds","CreatedById":50204,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-11T01:00:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224015068\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022137830\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221628186886\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022212916\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SnipersLaww\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 8/5/2021 at 3:08 PM, SnipersLaww said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nis there a way to get the mouse circle and pointer\u00A0to appear for this if it isnt visible?\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIIRC if you press \u0022P\u0022 or \u0022O\u0022 should toggle the automatic controls on or off, the other will switch between modes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SnipersLaww","CreatedById":212916,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-09-01T06:13:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224017950\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022137830\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221628643600\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002250204\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022tetryds\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 8/10/2021 at 8:00 PM, tetryds said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIIRC if you press \u0022P\u0022 or \u0022O\u0022 should toggle the automatic controls on or off, the other will switch between modes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe controls worked fine... but the visual reference circles are not there.\u00A0 (this part)\u00A0 (and I have checked the folder for the mod and it does contain image files for these)\u003Cimg alt=\u0022e955e77dff.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002285.26\u0022 height=\u0022989\u0022 width=\u00221160\u0022 src=\u0022https://puu.sh/I841i/e955e77dff.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-09-01T06:14:06Z\u0022 title=\u002209/01/2021 06:14  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 1, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by SnipersLaww\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tetryds","CreatedById":50204,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-05T20:40:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/212916-sniperslaww/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022212916\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/212916-sniperslaww/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@SnipersLaww\u003C/a\u003Edo you have any other control mod installed? Did you install the whole package?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf it works you might be missing the aim image assets within your game, try installing it again or using an older version to see if it persists.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SovPenguin","CreatedById":211463,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-04T22:14:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAll crafts I\u0027ve tried this on so far dont work, it usually just overcorrects and wobbles around a lot.\u003Cbr\u003E\nAnything I missed?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tetryds","CreatedById":50204,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-08T22:12:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224051454\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022137830\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221636064044\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022211463\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SovPenguin\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 11/4/2021 at 7:14 PM, SovPenguin said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAll crafts I\u0027ve tried this on so far dont work, it usually just overcorrects and wobbles around a lot.\u003Cbr\u003E\nAnything I missed?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nToo much control authority, you might be used to it, but mostly unnecessary for actual flight.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDecrease the deflection angle of your control surfaces, especially canards, and have fewer of them if you have too many, that will help a lot.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI also recommend using whatever is the latest ongoing version of \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aerospace Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SovPenguin","CreatedById":211463,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-12-01T20:51:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224052705\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022137830\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221636409521\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002250204\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022tetryds\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 11/8/2021 at 11:12 PM, tetryds said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nToo much control authority, you might be used to it, but mostly unnecessary for actual flight.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDecrease the deflection angle of your control surfaces, especially canards, and have fewer of them if you have too many, that will help a lot.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI also recommend using whatever is the latest ongoing version of \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aerospace Research (mod)\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aerospace Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks, will try \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JonNZzin","CreatedById":219310,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-02-15T08:17:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis mod would be perfect if it work the same way as the Battlefield mouse controll while flying helicopters or jets\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222022-02-25T16:44:45Z\u0022 title=\u002202/25/2022 04:44  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 25, 2022\u003C/time\u003E by JonNZzin\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MrPoker","CreatedById":217728,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-05-08T01:59:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBest mod ever. Finally my rockets not flipping now. This is a must-need. Should be included in ksp 2.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"pepperjackspaceprogram","CreatedById":221706,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-07T07:47:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nsounds nice. time to use it.\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"bungling","CreatedById":222595,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-09-25T11:44:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nis this still being updated? it seems really cool but the last time the message was edited (for changelogs) was back in early 2022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbal410","CreatedById":212401,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-11-27T05:48:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\ndoes it work on the ground, and with rotating servos?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222022-11-27T17:05:53Z\u0022 title=\u002211/27/2022 05:05  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 27, 2022\u003C/time\u003E by Kerbal410\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"BoZo_Xo2","CreatedById":225039,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-09-14T04:34:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think Mr. Scumbag meant adding an option to disable the rolling altogether.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat would be a great feature for vacuum flight.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGary Come Home.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"john xina","CreatedById":231204,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-11-10T15:16:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy Target isn\u0027t getting displayed, i tried to change the opacity settings but it still won\u0027t show it, any ideas on how to fix that?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"darthvader15001","CreatedById":222173,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-05-19T12:05:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\ndoes this work with the newest version of ksp?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"darthvader15001","CreatedById":222173,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-05-22T11:54:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/129964-linuxgurugamer/?do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022129964\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/129964-linuxgurugamer/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@linuxgurugamer\u003C/a\u003E could you possibly adopt this mod and make it up to date?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"stk2008","CreatedById":162264,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-05-22T12:37:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh thanks for bumping this thread I was meant to ask could we get it so when a Kerbal goes unconscious mouse aim flight also stops working because as it stands now when that happens the keyboard inputs stop working as expected but mouse aim flight still allows me to control the craft.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nThanks in advance\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"darthvader15001","CreatedById":222173,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-05-22T22:43:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/162264-stk2008/?do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022162264\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/162264-stk2008/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@stk2008\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0do you use this mod on 1.12.5? Just wondering if it works.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Papa_Joe","CreatedById":10788,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-05-23T16:12:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi all.\u00A0 Guess I need to check the forums more often.\u00A0 Let me look at the latest version against 1.12.5.\u00A0 See what I can do.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Celeste","CreatedById":233713,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-05-26T12:34:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCould you change a few things?\u003Cbr\u003E\n1. Have some sort of indicator where your mouse is when its off the screen.\u003Cbr\u003E\n2. Have a type of sensitivity which changes how aggressively\u00A0 the craft points towards where your mosue is pointing, if im making a small adjustment, I\u0027d prefer a lower chance of overshooting.\u003Cbr\u003E\n3. When map view is open, temporarily disable MAF, since rotating the view or moving the mouse at all will still control your craft, and by the time you close the map view, its probably already too late.\u003Cbr\u003E\n4. Please get this on \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222024-05-27T14:49:16Z\u0022 title=\u002205/27/2024 02:49  PM\u0022 data-short=\u0022May 27\u0022\u003EMay 27\u003C/time\u003E by Celeste\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}